# Control Document discusion

For my two games from Shake that Button, I reviewd Cairns, and Rustle your leaves to me softly. I didn't have any particular reason behind my choice other than they seemed interesting.

Cairn was a game about exploring a fictional universe. It was interesting because the main mechanic required a whole lot of pysical movement and interaction between two players to "win." It made use of the kinect to capture body geatures and positions to move a creature between these "portal" worlds, and was aimed more as an artistic installation, than a regular game. Which I thought was neat!

The other game "Rustle your leaves to me softly" was also just hilarious. ASMR Plant dating sim that creates instering soundscapes as you gently "explore" our celulous filled friends just sounds absurd. And it is!
